  "description": [
    "WATCH ON THE POTOMAC By ROBERT G SPIVACK Washington D C How To Make Neutrals Of Allies WASHINGTON D CThe United States government now has over 12000 men in South Viet Nam and spends over 1600000 daily to sup port the regime of NgoDinhDiem a tyrant who bears a close resemblance to the unlamented Cuban dictator Fulgencio Batista Diem who supposedly is fighting the Communist VietCong has been accused by the Democratic party of VietNam of imprisoning more than 105000 antiCommunist democrats in the past eight years and of putting somewhere between a halfmillion and a million of his countrymen in con centration camps The charges re main uncontradicted His opponents accuse him of spending about 100000 yearly on public relations in the United States The figures are conserva tive Since Diem has already col lected about two billion dollars from U S it is reasonable to as sume that it is our money that is being used to tell us how lucky we are to have Diem on our side At the present time Diem is en gaged in a religious war with the Buddhists who make up 80 per cent of the population Some idea of how intense"
  ],
